  <title>axial chirality</title>
  <termversion>2.3.3</termversion>
  <lastupdated>2014-02-24</lastupdated>
  <definitions>
    <item>
      <id>1</id>
      <text>Term used to refer to stereoisomerism resulting from the non-planar arrangement of four groups in pairs about a chirality axis. It is exemplified by allenesabC=C=Ccd (or abC=C=Cab) and by the atropisomerism of ortho-substituted biphenyls. The configuration in molecular entities possessing axial chirality is specified by the stereodescriptors Ra and Sa (or by P or M). [image: Not defined]</text>
